ci: refactor Docker workflows for efficiency and consistency
- Establish `.prettierrc` file under `.github/workflows` for consistent code formatting, setting tab width to 2 and disabling the use of tabs - Introduce a new reusable GitHub workflow for docker - Inputs received include Docker Hub and Quay registry credentials, along with the user-defined docker image tag - Docker registries logged into are Docker Hub, GHCR, and Quay - Metadata for docker images are being generated - Docker images can now be built and pushed to registries for both standard and UBI configurations - Modify the `docker_publish.yml` workflow to use the newly created reusable docker workflow instead of duplicating steps - GITHUB_TOKEN permissions are explicitly set for the actions in the `docker_publish.yml` workflow - Several steps in `docker_publish.yml` have been removed as they are now included in the reusable docker workflow file, making the workflow cleaner and more efficient.
Signed-off-by: 陳鈞 <jim60105@gmail.com>

feat: rewrite Dockerfile
- Added DL3008 rule to the Hadolint configuration. Now the linting requires explicit version pinning in `apt-get install` commands. - Updated the Dockerfile significantly: - Python version is raised from `3.11` to `3.12`. - Switched from `alpine` to `debian:bookworm-slim` as a base image. - Added a new `build` stage and separated the stages into "Build", "Compile with Nuitka", "Report", and "Final". - Added and updated various build libraries and cleaned up the process. - Updated the permissions and paths for various steps, improved cache utilization. - `ffmpeg` source is updated. - Libraries for `libxcb1` and `curl` are installed. - The final image is now labeled with metadata. - Updated the `record_twitcast.sh` script to execute `main.bin` instead of `main.py`.
Signed-off-by: 陳鈞 <jim60105@gmail.com>

chore: update submodule reference in `twitcasting-recorder`
- Update the subproject commit in `twitcasting-recorder`
Signed-off-by: 陳鈞 <jim60105@gmail.com>

Commented on #15536 [Feature Request]: 能否将扩展插件安装在其单独的虚拟环境里？Can the extension be installed in its own virtual environment?

每个torch包需要3.6G的磁盘空间，因此三个需要torch的扩展需要10G。
好的解决方案是所有扩展都必须使其依赖项与主项目保持一致。
这个方案好是好，只是从web端直接搜索安装会比较方便可是也会在web端安装扩展的依赖时导致主项目崩溃，然后就要重新调试。您的意思是不是：直接下载想要的扩展的源代码包，然后修改requirements.txt文件之后，再从本地安装呢？望不吝赐教，谢谢!
The maintainer of the extension SHOULD maintain its consistency. Of course, you can open an issue or a PR to fix it. This is how we play in open source.
